  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Indeed, one study of NER annotation speed found it can take between 10 and 30 seconds per sentence for experts to annotate named entities [8].",
    "The gold-standard annotated BioSemantics corpus is composed of 163,219 sentences, which implies an optimal annotation time of over 11 weeks at 40 hours per week (453.39 h) [20].",
    "This estimate, of course, excludes the time required for annotator training and interannotator reliability assessments, and because fine-tuning adjusts many or all of the model's parameters, it consumes computational resources.",
    "Time and power consumption for fine-tuning scales with training data size [21,22] and with the size of the underlying model that is computed.",
    "As of the date of writing, for example, it would be unrealistic to fine-tune very large models such as GPT-4.These limitations notwithstanding, it is increasingly recognized that long-standing presumptions about sufficiently large training data sets are likely substantially inflated [23]."
  ],
